result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Daniel David Dagastino was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Amphetamine/LSD/Psilocin, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(d).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Apprs: CO: SRN, Rpr: Kasten, Clerk: Scobey. ADA:  Amber L Hahn   DF ATTY:  Barry Curtis Lundeen   DF:  Daniel David Dagastino appeared. Case called at 11:42 a.m. Set for plea. Atty Lundeen states Diversion agreement in Ct 1 and DE will to plead to Amended Cts 2 and 3. Side bar. Recalled at 11:44 a.m. DE pleads no contest to Ct 1, DE pleads no contest to Amended Ct 2 and DE pleads no contest to Amended Ct 3. DE sworn. Court informs DE of rights. Attorneys stipulate to the facts. Court finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly makes plea. Court accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct 1. Court withholds entry of judgment in favor of DJOC in Ct 1.  Court finds DE guilty of Amended Cts 2 and 3. Recommendations. DE would like to serve probation in Pierce County. DE makes statement.
Court orders sentence:  W/H 2 years probation with conditions. Concurrent on each count but without prejudice to consecutive if revoked.

Conditions of probation are:

-AODA and follow any recommended treatment.  
-Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.
-Court costs of $443.00 on each count. DE to pay today.
-Regular and random testing by the Agent.
-3 months condition time - STAYED. To be used at the discretion of the Agent.
